Hide stock status bar editor / keyboard-layout items (PRO-5559)

The RudderStack "IDE Footer" design (Figma node 101-3202) keeps only the
git branch, problems counts and notifications bell. Items added by
VS Code's built-in editor-status contribution and by the web keyboard
layout picker have no configuration toggle, so we short-circuit the
registration paths to drop them.

For `editorStatus.ts`, each affected update* method has its body replaced
with just a clear() on the MutableDisposable so that nothing leaks into
the status bar; the surrounding state-tracking logic and command palette
commands stay intact. The bodies are fully replaced (not prepended with
`return;`) to avoid TS7027 under `allowUnreachableCode: false`.

For `keyboardLayoutPicker.ts`, the class is left fully intact and only
the `registerWorkbenchContribution2(...)` call is commented out so the
contribution never instantiates. Emptying the constructor body left the
imports / fields / DI params unused, which trips TS6133/TS6138 under the
project's `noUnusedLocals: true`; commenting out the registration sidesteps
all of that by simply not running the constructor at all. The picker
quick-open command (registered via `registerAction2` further down the file)
stays wired up so power users can still invoke it from the command palette.

Users can still re-enable any of these items by overriding the relevant
settings (where they exist) or by carrying their own fork.

